<p><b>Prof. Daniel Thalmann</b> is a Swiss and Canadian Computer Scientist and a pioneer in <a href="/wiki/Virtual_human" title="Virtual human" class="mw-redirect">Virtual Humans</a>. He is one of the most highly cited scientists in <a href="/wiki/Computer_Graphics" title="Computer Graphics" class="mw-redirect">Computer Graphics</a>.<sup id="cite_ref-1" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-1"><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup><sup id="cite_ref-2" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-2"><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> He is currently with the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://imi.ntu.edu.sg/Pages/Home.aspx">Institute for Media Innovation</a>, <a href="/wiki/Nanyang_Technological_University" title="Nanyang Technological University">Nanyang Technological University</a> in <a href="/wiki/Singapore" title="Singapore">Singapore</a> and Honorary Professor at <a href="/wiki/EPFL" title="EPFL" class="mw-redirect">EPFL</a>, <a href="/wiki/Switzerland" title="Switzerland">Switzerland</a>.</p>
<p></p>
